WEBVTT

00:01.042 --> 00:02.877
(Tessa)
Daddy had decided
to blend families

00:02.919 --> 00:03.878
with my high-school nemesis.

00:03.920 --> 00:05.005
Our house closed

00:05.046 --> 00:06.464
and so did our conversations.

00:06.506 --> 00:08.174
So, what's the plan
here, Tess?

00:08.216 --> 00:09.801
You still have another
year of school.

00:09.843 --> 00:11.386
Live with my grandmother,
commute to Chatswin

00:11.428 --> 00:12.971
finish up, get the hell out.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.889
You gonna tell me I can't?
'Cause I'm almost 18.

00:14.931 --> 00:17.892
No, I am not saying you can't.
I'm saying I wish you wouldn't.

00:17.934 --> 00:19.477
There's lots of things
I wish you wouldn't do

00:19.519 --> 00:21.021
like continue to make decisions

00:21.062 --> 00:22.689
with no regard for my feelings.

00:22.731 --> 00:25.483
I know that's what it seems like
I'm doing but I assure you--

00:25.525 --> 00:27.819
Why don't you just keep
telling yourself that, George?

00:27.861 --> 00:29.779
'Cause I'm not gonna
be around to hear it.

00:29.821 --> 00:31.906
Tessa! Tessa.

00:31.948 --> 00:34.701
Hope the three of you are happy
together. Have a nice life.

00:34.743 --> 00:36.494
Oh, and Dalia
doesn't even like you.

00:36.536 --> 00:38.163
She's just using you
to make her real dad jealous.

00:38.204 --> 00:39.414
- So good luck with that!
- Tessa!

00:39.456 --> 00:41.082
Can I just say
that I didn't know

00:41.124 --> 00:42.500
what was going on
with you and Dalia?

00:42.542 --> 00:44.627
Had I known,
I-I never would've accept..

00:47.839 --> 00:49.632
[sighs]

00:49.674 --> 00:51.760
[instrumental music]

00:51.801 --> 00:54.679
I've never seen her
like this before.

00:54.721 --> 00:55.805
- Are we making a mistake?
- Mm.

00:55.847 --> 00:57.057
Maybe this is all too much.

00:57.098 --> 00:59.601
No, no, I-I read
every one of those books

00:59.642 --> 01:01.436
that Sheila gave me and they all
said the same thing.

01:01.478 --> 01:03.313
You can't let the kids
call the shots.

01:03.354 --> 01:07.192
We as parents have to do
what's right for the family.

01:07.233 --> 01:09.360
What if we're wrong
about what's right?

01:12.947 --> 01:14.699
Daddy Altman?

01:19.120 --> 01:21.831
Since we're gonna be
one big happy family now

01:21.873 --> 01:24.542
will you take me to the
Father Daughter Purity Ball?

01:24.584 --> 01:25.585
The what?

01:26.920 --> 01:29.464
The Father Daughter Purity Ball.

01:31.007 --> 01:34.552
This is our chance
to restore decency

01:34.594 --> 01:37.097
to take our daughters
gently by the weave

01:37.138 --> 01:39.390
and say, "Slow down,
you little ratchet."

01:39.432 --> 01:41.309
Hmm.

01:41.351 --> 01:43.728
Do the girls have
to be pure to attend?

01:43.770 --> 01:46.147
Because I'm not showing any
virgins currently enrolled here.

01:46.189 --> 01:49.067
Oh, I think we have
at least one.

01:49.109 --> 01:52.070
But I'm not here to boast
about Lisa's late-blooming.

01:52.112 --> 01:54.114
The times they have a-changed

01:54.155 --> 01:55.949
and it is up to us

01:55.990 --> 01:57.700
to a-change them back.

01:57.742 --> 02:00.703
[theme music]

02:00.745 --> 02:05.834
♪ Last night I had
a pleasant nightmare ♪

02:05.875 --> 02:08.503
♪ Da-da-da da da-da-da da ♪♪

02:08.545 --> 02:10.088
[phone ringing]

02:10.130 --> 02:11.756
Hi, grandma. It's me, Tessa.

02:11.798 --> 02:13.842
Tessa! Are you well?

02:13.883 --> 02:15.552
I'm okay. I've been better.

02:15.593 --> 02:16.594
Um..

02:16.636 --> 02:18.179
'I need something, I mean..'

02:18.221 --> 02:19.430
I mean, I need..

02:19.472 --> 02:21.641
..you, if possible.

02:21.683 --> 02:24.144
Tessa, you're making me nervous.

02:24.185 --> 02:26.062
- What's going on?
- It's nothing.

02:26.104 --> 02:28.606
It's just...my dad.

02:28.648 --> 02:30.984
'I don't want to live
with him anymore'

02:31.025 --> 02:32.318
'which is why I was wondering'

02:32.360 --> 02:35.113
if it might be possible for..

02:35.155 --> 02:36.781
...me to come live
with you next year.

02:36.823 --> 02:38.241
Well, you know

02:38.283 --> 02:41.369
I'm not really set up
for a second person.

02:41.411 --> 02:44.164
'You know, with just
the one bathroom.'

02:44.205 --> 02:46.958
Oh, sweetie, I hate
to disappoint you.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.419
'How about you come again
for part of the summer?'

02:49.460 --> 02:51.254
Is it okay if I call
you back later?

02:51.296 --> 02:53.214
(Helen)
'O-o-okay. Bye-bye.'

02:53.840 --> 02:55.592
[beeps]

02:58.178 --> 03:00.722
Mom? Who was that?

03:00.763 --> 03:02.724
[Daughter singing "Landfill"]

03:02.765 --> 03:04.100
Tessa.

03:06.936 --> 03:09.689
(Tessa)
Since grand-mama had left me
for the wolves

03:09.731 --> 03:11.524
I sought refuge
in the one place

03:11.566 --> 03:14.402
that I had always felt safe.

03:14.444 --> 03:18.239
♪ Push me out to sea ♪

03:18.281 --> 03:22.160
♪ On a little boat
that you made out ♪♪

03:22.202 --> 03:24.370
You're leaving.

03:24.412 --> 03:26.122
She's leaving.

03:28.291 --> 03:29.751
What's gonna happen to me?

03:29.792 --> 03:32.045
You'll be fine.

03:32.086 --> 03:34.130
You'll be..

03:34.172 --> 03:36.758
...queen of the Purity Ball.

03:36.799 --> 03:40.094
Mm, well, technically,
that's impossible.

03:40.136 --> 03:42.764
Malik's been buttering
my bread since President's day.

03:44.057 --> 03:45.850
Don't tell mom.

03:45.892 --> 03:47.268
[birds chirping]

03:47.310 --> 03:48.728
[instrumental music]

03:48.770 --> 03:50.438
(George)
I believe I am in boxes again.

03:50.480 --> 03:52.190
I feel like I just got
out of boxes.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.359
[gasps]
OMG! George! Look.

03:54.400 --> 03:58.404
This one in Chatswin Hills has
a custom leather living room.

03:58.446 --> 04:00.114
Leather living room?

04:00.156 --> 04:01.950
It's a work of art.

04:01.991 --> 04:03.451
It's an overpriced wooden box.

04:03.493 --> 04:05.286
Look at the square footage.
It's tiny.

04:05.328 --> 04:06.871
Check out the lot size.

04:06.913 --> 04:09.916
- We could always expand.
- We could expand.

04:09.958 --> 04:12.377
What kind of couch would you
put in a leather living room?

04:12.418 --> 04:15.672
Me, I'd probably do
a marble sectional.

04:15.713 --> 04:17.298
[chuckles]
Sounds comfy.

04:17.340 --> 04:19.801
[instrumental music]

04:19.842 --> 04:21.469
(Tessa)
While George and Dallas
were out looking

04:21.511 --> 04:23.221
for a new love nest

04:23.263 --> 04:25.640
I was adjusting to life
in the toilet.

04:28.351 --> 04:30.937
Oh. This looks lovely.

04:30.979 --> 04:32.522
- Thank you.
- Welcome.

04:36.651 --> 04:40.029
Mmm. So does your dad know
you're living in a restroom?

04:40.071 --> 04:41.072
He thinks I'm at Helen's.

04:41.114 --> 04:42.240
Why don't you stay at our place?

04:42.282 --> 04:44.534
Because, Lisa.

04:44.575 --> 04:46.661
- Because.
- Yeah. No. That's true.

04:46.703 --> 04:49.455
I'm just tired of it, you know?

04:49.497 --> 04:51.457
I'm tired of everybody expecting

04:51.499 --> 04:53.876
I'm just gonna do whatever
the hell they want.

04:53.918 --> 04:56.087
And that I'm just gonna
grin and bear it?

04:56.129 --> 04:58.298
Well, I'm done grinning
and I'm done bearing it.

04:58.339 --> 04:59.799
You should see this dress
that my mother wants me to wear

04:59.841 --> 05:01.426
to this Purity Ball of hers.

05:01.467 --> 05:02.802
It's a frickin' bridal gown.

05:02.844 --> 05:05.847
Do they not realize that
we are almost adults?

05:05.888 --> 05:07.724
They can't just tell us
how it's gonna be anymore.

05:07.765 --> 05:09.475
And we're not
just gonna choke down

05:09.517 --> 05:11.978
a cup of undercooked neon
noodles just to avoid

05:12.020 --> 05:14.564
hurting some homeless
woman's feelings.

05:16.607 --> 05:18.901
That was delicious, though.
Thank you.

05:18.943 --> 05:21.112
[instrumental music]

05:21.154 --> 05:22.363
(Dallas)
'But, George..

05:22.405 --> 05:24.365
- Leather living room!
- I know.

05:24.407 --> 05:26.159
And did you see
that lighting fixture?

05:26.200 --> 05:28.786
It was rustic meets sparkly.

05:28.828 --> 05:30.997
It was the perfect
representation of us.

05:31.039 --> 05:33.333
Well, maybe we can find
a lighting fixture like that

05:33.374 --> 05:35.084
and put it in a house
that's still on the market

05:35.126 --> 05:37.420
because that one
has an accepted offer.

05:37.462 --> 05:39.797
Unless you wanna put
in a backup offer.

05:39.839 --> 05:41.799
Yeah, but you don't love it.

05:41.841 --> 05:44.218
Well, no, but, uh,
I could live with it.

05:44.260 --> 05:46.012
I could learn to love it.

05:46.054 --> 05:48.139
[instrumental music]

05:48.181 --> 05:50.308
Oh, I gotta get going. Ahem.

05:50.350 --> 05:51.601
'I gotta run by home
and get ready'

05:51.642 --> 05:53.853
for my big date with Dalia.

05:55.313 --> 05:56.481
- Um, George?
- Yeah?

05:56.522 --> 05:57.690
Can I be honest with you?

05:57.732 --> 05:59.609
I'm not real sure
you should be taking

05:59.650 --> 06:01.069
Dalia to this event.

06:01.110 --> 06:03.363
Dalia wants to go. If I
don't take her, who will?

06:03.404 --> 06:05.406
[instrumental music]

06:05.448 --> 06:07.241
[gasps]

06:09.744 --> 06:11.579
Hi, Dallas.
That's a nice dress.

06:11.621 --> 06:13.414
Is it Cavalli?

06:18.503 --> 06:19.921
(Steven)
'He's not her father.'

06:19.962 --> 06:21.631
He can't be parading around
like he's her father.

06:21.672 --> 06:23.883
Steven, you need to find
another way to express yourself.

06:23.925 --> 06:25.385
You can't go around
punching people.

06:25.426 --> 06:26.761
I don't go around
punching people.

06:26.803 --> 06:28.763
I just punch him.
I-I don't know what it is.

06:28.805 --> 06:29.972
I just find him very punchable.

06:30.014 --> 06:31.224
Mommy, is he okay?

06:31.265 --> 06:32.558
Yeah, he's, he's okay.

06:32.600 --> 06:34.477
Hey, you leave
my daughter alone!

06:34.519 --> 06:36.104
I thought that was your job.

06:36.145 --> 06:37.397
- Aah!
- Ooh!

06:37.438 --> 06:39.357
Daddies, stop fighting over me.

06:39.399 --> 06:40.650
What are you doing here anyway?

06:40.691 --> 06:42.485
I thought you were off
living in Singapore.

06:42.527 --> 06:44.695
I am in Singapore!
Ooh! Hey!

06:44.737 --> 06:47.281
That reminds me,
my beautiful wife, Wan'er.

06:47.323 --> 06:49.158
Come on.

06:49.200 --> 06:50.993
- Hello.
- Hello.

06:51.035 --> 06:52.370
I want that tiny hat.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.996
Sweetheart, give her
the tiny hat.

06:54.038 --> 06:55.123
- No.
- Yes.

06:55.164 --> 06:57.417
Wan'er, I've heard so much.

06:58.793 --> 07:00.461
Hey, George,
sorry about the punching

07:00.503 --> 07:03.089
but I need to impress upon you
that I am her father.

07:03.131 --> 07:05.049
Just because I'm not around
doesn't give you the right--

07:05.091 --> 07:08.970
Yes, it does! It gives me
every right, you big baby.

07:09.011 --> 07:11.806
Being a father
isn't a title you hold

07:11.848 --> 07:13.349
like a some fighter's belt.

07:13.391 --> 07:15.560
It's an active job and if you
aren't there to do it

07:15.601 --> 07:18.312
somebody else has to.
Ugh! Aah-ha!

07:18.354 --> 07:19.939
Stop hitting, Daddy Altman.

07:19.981 --> 07:21.816
You stop calling him that!

07:21.858 --> 07:23.526
I'm so starving, you guys.

07:23.568 --> 07:25.736
- Can we go get sushi?
- I could do sushi.

07:25.778 --> 07:28.948
George? Rainbow roll?

07:28.990 --> 07:31.409
I don't think George
feels like a rainbow roll.

07:31.451 --> 07:34.328
[instrumental music]

07:35.204 --> 07:37.165
[sighs]

07:41.961 --> 07:43.421
Whoa.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.047
Sheila, we have a doorbell!

07:45.089 --> 07:46.716
As your broker,
I wouldn't have let myself in

07:46.757 --> 07:49.010
if it wasn't important,
and it is.

07:49.051 --> 07:50.219
The place you saw today?

07:50.261 --> 07:52.054
That place Dallas
fell in love with?

07:52.096 --> 07:53.389
The offer fell through.

07:53.431 --> 07:54.932
They couldn't get their
financing together.

07:54.974 --> 07:56.809
I-I cannot think about
this right now, Sheila.

07:56.851 --> 07:58.311
- I have a face wound.
- Okay.

07:58.352 --> 08:00.396
Okay, fine. Let's
weigh all the options.

08:00.438 --> 08:01.772
You can rent something

08:01.814 --> 08:03.608
and flush your money
down the toilet.

08:03.649 --> 08:05.818
You can move in with Dallas
and be her bitch. I mean..

08:07.612 --> 08:09.155
Or I can man up
and buy the place

08:09.197 --> 08:10.448
my lady is crazy about.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.533
It is squeaky-clean, George.

08:12.575 --> 08:14.702
Copper piping.
Closets by Claudia.

08:14.744 --> 08:18.372
- Claudia?
- And it is a massive lot.

08:18.414 --> 08:20.917
Mature trees.
Dogwoods up the wazoo.

08:20.958 --> 08:23.753
- You know something, Sheila?
- What?

08:23.794 --> 08:25.338
You're good at your job.

08:25.379 --> 08:28.799
(Sheila)
How does she do it, folks?

08:28.841 --> 08:30.468
She kills it on the work front

08:30.510 --> 08:32.178
she crushes it at home

08:32.220 --> 08:34.430
and in her spare time..

08:34.472 --> 08:36.724
Fred? Why aren't you two
dressed for the Purity Ball?

08:36.766 --> 08:38.601
- 'You're gonna be late.'
- Have a seat, dear.

08:38.643 --> 08:39.977
No, I will not have a seat.

08:40.019 --> 08:41.270
'Our community is expecting me'

08:41.312 --> 08:42.897
just as they are expecting
the two of you.

08:42.939 --> 08:44.815
Well, Sheila, I do
believe their expectations

08:44.857 --> 08:46.442
are not going to be met.

08:46.484 --> 08:48.819
Not tonight. Lisa?

08:50.613 --> 08:54.408
Lisa! You're finally gonna be
the queen of something.

08:54.450 --> 08:56.285
You're a lock!

08:56.327 --> 08:58.162
Yeah, that's the thing, mother.

08:59.705 --> 09:02.959
- I'm not a lock.
- Oh. You are too a lock.

09:03.918 --> 09:05.503
She's not a lock, Mrs. Shay.

09:05.545 --> 09:08.381
[dramatic music]

09:12.009 --> 09:13.386
Oh, I see.

09:13.427 --> 09:15.054
This is your way of telling me

09:15.096 --> 09:17.014
the two of you have been
engaging in premarital sex.

09:17.056 --> 09:18.975
- Is that it, Lisa?
- No.

09:19.016 --> 09:20.393
No, I've never had sex.

09:20.434 --> 09:23.145
[chuckles]
Oh, oh, thank God!

09:23.187 --> 09:24.605
But I have made love.

09:24.647 --> 09:26.857
[retching]
Ooh, Fred, the bucket!

09:26.899 --> 09:30.236
I can't fathom why
you would need a bucket, mother.

09:30.278 --> 09:32.530
I love Malik
and Malik loves me.

09:32.572 --> 09:35.533
and we've made love
to each other many, many times

09:35.575 --> 09:38.119
and it's been fantastic.

09:38.160 --> 09:41.497
Welp, congratulations, Lisa.

09:41.539 --> 09:44.417
One of your most redeeming
qualities isn't yours after all.

09:48.671 --> 09:50.548
[sighs]
Oh, well..

09:53.801 --> 09:55.803
My first time was with a girl

09:55.845 --> 09:57.805
I wasn't really in love with.

09:59.181 --> 10:02.101
[sighs]
And although I grew

10:02.143 --> 10:04.770
to care deeply for your mother

10:04.812 --> 10:06.439
there are times
I wish I'd trained

10:06.480 --> 10:08.566
with someone a bit more tender.

10:08.608 --> 10:11.027
- You know?
- Yeah.

10:11.068 --> 10:13.487
So bless you both..

10:13.529 --> 10:16.490
...for being brave enough
to follow your hearts.

10:16.532 --> 10:18.409
(Tessa)
With Lisa out of the picture

10:18.451 --> 10:21.078
Sheila had to cast
her net a little wider.

10:21.120 --> 10:23.164
Inside every girl

10:23.205 --> 10:25.166
is a beautiful gift.

10:25.207 --> 10:26.500
Where's the gift from?

10:26.542 --> 10:28.419
Is it from the juniors' section?

10:28.461 --> 10:30.588
No, it's not
from the juniors' section.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.882
The point is, the gift

10:32.923 --> 10:34.884
must never be given away.

10:34.925 --> 10:36.594
Oh, snizz!

10:36.636 --> 10:37.970
That's my jam right there!

10:38.012 --> 10:40.306
[Big Sean
singing "Dance (A$$)"]

10:42.683 --> 10:44.810
Girls, stop that!

10:44.852 --> 10:48.147
No female role model
has the last name "Minaj."

10:49.649 --> 10:52.360
♪ Go stupid go stupid ♪

10:52.401 --> 10:54.779
(Tessa)
Thanks to the Purity Ball,
I had music.

10:54.820 --> 10:56.030
I was getting three squares

10:56.072 --> 10:57.406
out the school vending machine.

10:57.448 --> 10:58.991
I'd never been better.

10:59.033 --> 11:01.243
♪ Wobble wobble
I'm sta-stacking my paper ♪

11:01.285 --> 11:02.953
♪ My wallet look
like a bible ♪♪

11:05.956 --> 11:06.957
What are you doing here?

11:06.999 --> 11:08.000
I just wanted to tell you

11:08.042 --> 11:10.294
that I'm glad that we broke up.

11:10.336 --> 11:12.505
Cool. So am I.

11:12.546 --> 11:14.965
It's gonna make it a lot easier
for me to leave for college

11:15.007 --> 11:17.051
now that we're no longer
in love.

11:17.093 --> 11:19.720
Great. So leave.

11:19.762 --> 11:21.430
I will.

11:21.472 --> 11:23.933
The door's right here.

11:23.974 --> 11:26.602
[Joe Purdy singing
"Mary May & Bobby"]

11:32.858 --> 11:34.819
That's not how you leave.

11:34.860 --> 11:36.529
You don't know how I leave.

11:36.570 --> 11:40.116
♪ It was a fine day
in the fifth grade ♪

11:41.951 --> 11:47.206
♪ When Mary May let Bobby
walk her home from school♪

11:47.248 --> 11:48.749
♪ And he loved the way ♪

11:48.791 --> 11:51.043
♪ Her hair fell
across her dress ♪♪

11:51.085 --> 11:54.505
(Tessa)
Ironically, the playlist
for the Purity Ball

11:54.547 --> 11:57.299
was incredibly romantic.

12:04.515 --> 12:05.474
[Chapin Sisters
singing" Toxic"]

12:18.738 --> 12:20.781
♪ Baby can't you see ♪

12:20.823 --> 12:22.491
♪ I'm calling ♪

12:22.533 --> 12:23.951
♪ A guy like you ♪

12:23.993 --> 12:27.037
♪ Should wear a warning
it's dangerous ♪♪

12:27.079 --> 12:29.123
(Tessa)
Sometimes..

12:29.165 --> 12:31.584
...when you want something
to be true..

12:31.625 --> 12:34.253
Alright, there's a little
step coming up right now.

12:34.295 --> 12:35.921
You'll do anything

12:35.963 --> 12:38.424
to convince yourself
that it is.

12:38.466 --> 12:40.676
And sometimes..

12:40.718 --> 12:44.096
...even a blindfold
can't stop you from..

12:44.138 --> 12:46.724
...seeing things clearly.

12:52.062 --> 12:54.064
Those better be tears of joy.

12:56.901 --> 12:59.570
We got the place, Dallas.
It's ours.

13:00.821 --> 13:02.823
George, I can't.

13:02.865 --> 13:04.784
You..

13:04.825 --> 13:06.869
You're kidding right now.

13:06.911 --> 13:08.329
I know you did this for me.

13:08.370 --> 13:10.748
I know you do
everything for me.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.374
- But in your heart--
- You're not kidding.

13:12.416 --> 13:14.293
- In your heart--
- Are you crazy?

13:14.335 --> 13:16.504
- In your heart--
- Don't tell what's in my heart!

13:16.545 --> 13:18.130
Dallas, what?

13:18.172 --> 13:20.591
I bought a house with..

13:20.633 --> 13:22.927
...a leather living room.

13:22.968 --> 13:24.887
My own daughter hates my guts!

13:24.929 --> 13:26.806
I know!

13:26.847 --> 13:29.099
And I know you've been trying
real hard to prove everything

13:29.141 --> 13:32.394
and that's exactly
what it feels like, George.

13:32.436 --> 13:34.730
I am like this house.

13:34.772 --> 13:37.775
You learned to love me.

13:37.817 --> 13:41.320
But it's not the same thing
as being in love with me.

13:41.362 --> 13:43.656
You aren't.

13:43.697 --> 13:45.658
And I don't think
you ever were.

13:47.535 --> 13:49.411
You know something?

13:50.746 --> 13:52.915
You're the one

13:52.957 --> 13:55.292
that doesn't love you, Dallas.

13:55.334 --> 13:56.418
You.

13:58.170 --> 13:59.630
And that's why

13:59.672 --> 14:01.882
you have sabotaged this
at every turn.

14:01.924 --> 14:05.094
I have jumped
through every freaking hoop

14:05.135 --> 14:07.346
and you keep moving the hoop!

14:13.686 --> 14:16.188
I'm never gonna convince you,
am I?

14:18.524 --> 14:20.192
I'm sorry.

14:25.364 --> 14:27.741
(George)
Oh, I-I agree.
This is very sorry.

14:27.783 --> 14:29.451
You know, I-I should've
listened to Tessa.

14:29.493 --> 14:31.036
She told me Dalia
was trying to play

14:31.078 --> 14:32.496
Steven and me
against each other.

14:32.538 --> 14:34.540
She had her dad fly
in to punch me out?

14:34.582 --> 14:35.583
What, did that give her some
kind of weird satisfaction?

14:35.624 --> 14:37.084
I had her father fly in!

14:37.126 --> 14:39.044
I called Steven. I did.

14:39.086 --> 14:41.297
[birds chirping]

14:41.338 --> 14:42.381
Why?

14:44.049 --> 14:46.927
Because I didn't want her
feeling attached to you anymore.

14:54.226 --> 14:56.353
How did this happen?

14:56.395 --> 14:57.980
[car engine turns over]

14:58.022 --> 14:59.523
'Well, I'll tell you one thing.'

14:59.565 --> 15:01.692
There's no way
that lighting fixture stays!

15:01.734 --> 15:03.277
You hear me?

15:03.319 --> 15:05.654
I'm getting rid of that
ugly-ass chandelier

15:05.696 --> 15:07.281
that represents us!

15:07.323 --> 15:09.867
[instrumental music]

15:18.208 --> 15:21.045
[panting]

15:21.086 --> 15:22.546
You're going down.

15:22.588 --> 15:25.507
[grunts]

15:27.760 --> 15:29.845
Ugh! Alright.

15:29.887 --> 15:31.055
I got you now

15:31.096 --> 15:33.807
you tacky, gaudy, ugly-ass

15:33.849 --> 15:35.267
son of a.. Aah!

15:35.309 --> 15:37.186
[grunts]

15:38.395 --> 15:40.940
[birds chirping]

15:45.069 --> 15:47.780
[panting]

15:47.821 --> 15:49.573
[dog barking in distance]

15:49.615 --> 15:51.033
[The Chapin Sisters
singing "Shady River]"

15:51.075 --> 15:53.077
What the hell are you
looking at?

15:57.456 --> 15:59.667
[instrumental music]

16:02.086 --> 16:07.675
♪ Sunny morning
sunny afternoon ♪

16:09.134 --> 16:12.054
♪ When it's always June ♪

16:12.096 --> 16:15.849
♪ There's no time to cry ♪

16:18.435 --> 16:21.397
♪ Days keep passing ♪

16:21.438 --> 16:25.776
♪ But they're all the same ♪

16:25.818 --> 16:27.236
♪ Seasons never change.. ♪♪

16:27.277 --> 16:29.279
You better not be a girl.

16:31.031 --> 16:32.199
Good.

16:34.868 --> 16:36.453
Let's go.

16:43.669 --> 16:45.087
(Tessa)
I didn't bother waking
Ryan up to say good-bye.

16:45.129 --> 16:47.840
We'd already said good-bye.

16:47.881 --> 16:49.049
He was going his way

16:49.091 --> 16:51.343
and I was bound to go mine.

16:51.385 --> 16:55.014
I just didn't know which way
I was going. Not yet.

16:55.055 --> 17:00.019
♪ Oh from the first
that the line got drawn ♪

17:00.060 --> 17:02.938
Hey, third cousin Jeff.

17:02.980 --> 17:04.940
It's me, Tessa.

17:06.608 --> 17:07.943
Altman?

17:11.613 --> 17:13.240
I understand.

17:14.491 --> 17:17.578
Yeah, anyway,
it was good to catch up.

17:17.619 --> 17:19.621
Yeah, and if your mom
changes her mind..

17:21.373 --> 17:23.792
Okay. Thanks, Rosie.

17:23.834 --> 17:26.295
Hey, uh..

17:26.336 --> 17:29.006
Do you know if Chelsea
has the same number?

17:30.174 --> 17:32.009
Okay.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.260
Thanks.

17:34.428 --> 17:37.139
♪ When you were the savior ♪

17:37.181 --> 17:40.392
♪ And I was the taker of ♪

17:44.313 --> 17:45.939
Hey!

17:45.981 --> 17:47.441
'Hey!'

17:47.483 --> 17:48.609
Oh, sorry. Not you.

17:48.650 --> 17:50.903
I think that's...my mother.

17:50.944 --> 17:53.322
- Oh. Hey!
- Hey!

17:53.363 --> 17:57.743
♪ Oh but man oh man ♪

17:57.785 --> 17:59.995
Um, excuse me. Sorry.

18:01.371 --> 18:03.707
Um...excuse me.

18:04.958 --> 18:07.461
♪ Oh man ♪

18:07.503 --> 18:08.504
- Alex.
- Hi!

18:08.545 --> 18:09.713
What are you doing here?

18:09.755 --> 18:12.091
I thought
you were back in Berlin.

18:12.132 --> 18:13.550
I was supposed to be

18:13.592 --> 18:16.386
but Berlin just seemed so far

18:16.428 --> 18:19.515
from things, so I-I thought
maybe I would

18:19.556 --> 18:21.934
try something else for a while.

18:21.975 --> 18:23.560
Chatswin?

18:23.602 --> 18:26.605
Look, Tessa, no pressure
whatsoever, really.

18:26.647 --> 18:28.524
I just wanted to be around

18:28.565 --> 18:30.526
in case you ever

18:30.567 --> 18:32.444
wanted me around.

18:35.364 --> 18:37.699
(Tessa)
For someone
who was never around

18:37.741 --> 18:39.743
she showed up at just
the right time.

18:39.785 --> 18:44.498
♪ I have to say
there was a mile or two ♪

18:44.540 --> 18:47.167
(Tessa on answering machine)
'Hey, it's Tessa.
Leave a message.'

18:47.209 --> 18:50.337
(George on answering machine)
'Hey, Tessa, it's your dad.'

18:50.379 --> 18:54.675
'I guess I just-I just
I'm-I'm calling 'cause'

18:54.716 --> 18:57.219
'I just wanna say..'

18:57.261 --> 18:59.346
'...sorry.'

18:59.388 --> 19:00.889
'I'm sorry.'

19:02.808 --> 19:04.685
You're sleeping over, right?

19:04.726 --> 19:06.395
[thud]

19:21.326 --> 19:22.786
I'm living here.

19:22.828 --> 19:24.079
No.

19:25.289 --> 19:27.666
But I want to.

19:27.708 --> 19:30.335
I know mommy doesn't want me
attached to you but..

19:31.837 --> 19:33.797
...it's kind of already
too late.

19:35.465 --> 19:37.509
You're a really good dad.

19:37.551 --> 19:41.805
I don't feel
like a...really good dad.

19:41.847 --> 19:43.891
But you are one.

19:45.100 --> 19:46.977
Can I sleep here one night?

19:47.019 --> 19:48.979
[dog whimpers]

19:52.149 --> 19:53.650
He'd like you to.

19:53.692 --> 19:55.694
Just, um..

19:55.736 --> 19:57.779
Let her know where you are.

20:01.450 --> 20:03.702
Carmen usually sings to me.

20:05.996 --> 20:07.331
Okay.

20:10.959 --> 20:12.961
What's your probs?

20:23.263 --> 20:24.723
[guitar music]

20:26.516 --> 20:32.481
♪ There's an ocean formed
outside my bedroom door ♪

20:32.522 --> 20:36.360
♪ On the sleepless nights
I listen to it roar ♪

20:38.445 --> 20:44.409
♪ There's a road too long
to walk too steep to climb ♪

20:44.451 --> 20:49.790
♪ At the end of it
is what you left behind ♪

20:49.831 --> 20:53.210
♪ And when that train rolls in ♪

20:53.252 --> 20:57.547
♪ If the doors open
don't get in ♪

20:57.589 --> 21:00.884
♪ Last night I had ♪

21:00.926 --> 21:04.137
♪ A pleasant nightmare ♪

